<p>Wednesday 2nd may 1917<br/>Leg stiff went up to Doctor.<br/>No duty for two days have to report to the Doctor on Friday morning.<br/>After dusk our guns started a very heavy bombardment, which was kept up all night. I am told that the great push starts tonight.<br/>This morning the Boys took most of our "Donks" up the line to the batteries as they were short of horses.</p>
